Rating: 4
I love this recipe! It is easy and tastes great! I use heavy cream instead of milk, but add a lot more vanilla. Use a good quality vanilla and real butter. I also add the vanilla before the sugar to help with the mixing. The butter has to be at room temp and creamed very well (fluffy) in order to incorporate all of the sugar, and beat it very well with the cream. It will be a beautiful, soft consistency. If you want to decorate with it, you have to cool it or add merengue powder to it, though I haven't tried this.

