Rating: 3
I thought this recipe was brilliant. It's far easier than many butter cream frosting recipes I've seen. I disagree with those who said to use 2.5 cups of powdered sugar; I used all four cups and found it to be perfect consistency (Frosting is going to be sweet no matter what you do to it, after all). The only modification I made was to use cream instead of milk. I've also found this recipe takes other flavours well; I made it with orange and orange-blossom water and it was marvelous.

Rating: 3
I like how simple this recipe is, and it's very easy to make minor adjustments for preference. I used margarine and 1.5% milk. I also replaced about 2dl of the sugar with vanilla sugar which isn't quite as sweet and has more vanilla flavour (this is a common ingredient in Scandinavia, not sure if it can be found elsewhere but definitely worth it). I added some flour to make it thicker and was liberal with the milk. Making it as is would be extremely sweet, and would taste basically just like powdered sugar, but everyone's frosting preferences are different so I think this recipe is a good a starting point.

