Rating: 3
I was looking for a white icing recipe that was quick - a full out buttercream is also a little too heavy and rich for my kids' 'birthday cake' tastes; so this seemed promising. Following the earlier reviews, I used 2.5 cups sugar - which was more than enough. I can't imagine using 4 c. I substituted 1 tsp white shortening for 1 tsp of the butter - after creaming the butter -to ensure creaminess for the kids and measured 1/3 c heavy cream instead of the milk, using almost all of it, while whipping the icing, to the consistency I liked. We used it to ice the white cupcakes recipe from epicurious - which is not too sweet and can handle a sweet icing. The end result was absolutely delicious and the kids adored it. I should mention that I used the whipping attachment on a kitchenaid stand mixer, which might have made a difference in the end result.

